{
  "local_port": 37638,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you get an ink stain out of fabric?",
  "response": "Removing ink stains from fabric can be challenging but there are several methods you can try:\n\n### 1. Rubbing Alcohol\n1. **Blot the Stain:** Place a paper towel or clean cloth underneath the stained area to prevent the ink from spreading.\n2. **Apply Alcohol:** Apply rubbing alcohol directly to the stain using a cotton ball or a clean cloth.\n3. **Blot Again:** Gently blot the stain with another clean cloth. You should see the ink start to transfer to the cloth.\n4. **Rinse:** Rinse the area with cool water.\n5. **Wash:** Launder as usual.\n\n### 2. Vinegar and Cornstarch\n1. **Mix Solution:** Combine two parts white vinegar with three parts cornstarch to form a paste.\n2. **Apply Paste:** Spread the paste over the stain.\n3. **Let Sit:** Allow the paste to dry completely.\n4. **Brush Off:** Once the paste is dry, brush it off.\n5. **Rinse:** Rinse the fabric with cool water.\n6. **Wash:** Launder as usual.\n\n### 3. Hairspray\n1. **Blot the Stain:** Place a paper towel underneath the stained area.\n2. **Spray Stain:** Spray the stain with hairspray (preferably alcohol-based).\n3. **Blot with Cloth:** Blot the stain with a clean cloth to lift the ink.\n4. **Rinse:** Rinse the area with cool water.\n5. **Wash:** Launder as usual.\n\n### 4. Dish Soap and Warm Water\n1. **Blot the Stain:** Place a paper towel underneath the stained area.\n2. **Apply Soap:** Apply a small amount of dish soap to the stain.\n3. **Rub Gently:** Rub gently with your fingers or a soft brush.\n4. **Rinse:** Rinse the area with warm water.\n5. **Wash:** Launder as usual.\n\n### 5. Commercial Stain Removers\n1. **Choose Remover:** Use a stain remover designed for ink stains, following the instructions on the label.\n2. **Apply Remover:** Apply the stain remover to the affected area.\n3. **Blot with Cloth:** Follow the instructions for blotting or rubbing.\n4. **Rinse:** Rinse the area with cool water.\n5. **Wash:** Launder as usual.\n\n### Tips\n- Test any solution on a small, inconspicuous area of the fabric first to ensure it doesn\u2019t cause damage or discoloration.\n- Act quickly; fresh ink stains are easier to remove than old ones.\n- Avoid heat, which can set the ink stain.\n\nBy trying one or a combination of these methods, you should be able to remove the ink stain from your fabric effectively.",
